<br>
There was a brief time (somewhere between 2 weeks and 2 months) after the destealth-through-damage patch went live when you couldn't use that technique for pulling because the mob would hit you as soon as it got in range, before you had a chance to hit them.<br>
<br>
Something was changed so that it works again now. They did a stealth change to the prediction code or to the range at which you melee a mob or added a delay to their initial attack. I'm not sure which of these methods was used to fix it (I suspect it was the prediction code), but it does work now.<br>
